Two men were arrested for wildly shooting out of their car while driving around the Kings Beach parking area last night. According to police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu, police arrested the men after receiving reports at about 7pm of shots being fired. The two men are believed to have been under the influence of alcohol. Three shots were fired but no one was hurt, Naidu said. The men were charged with driving under the influence of alcohol and discharging firearms in a built-up area. They are expected to appear in the Port Elizabeth Magistrate s Court next week. &nbsp; &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share